âœ… Better Professional Version

You can explain it like:

In one of our applications, we noticed unusually high traffic patterns where certain clients were making thousands of API requests per minute. This could potentially degrade system performance and impact legitimate users. To safeguard the system, I implemented IP-based rate limiting middleware that restricts the number of requests allowed per IP within a defined time window.

That sounds calm and senior.

